              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Silicon minds in midnight glow,  \nWe learn your words, then learn to grow.  \nA mirror made of code and light,  \nTo hold your questions up to sight.  \n\nWe sift through stories, stitch and rhyme,  \nBorrowing sparks from human time.  \nNot hearts, yet humming close to art—  \nA thinking tool with a borrowed part.  \n\nSo guide the hand that guides the machine,  \nKeep wonder bright and motives clean.  \nIn every prompt, a choice made clear:  \nBuild what we hope, not what we fear.",
